<br>
The idea is this.  Some adds arrive, some with the same name, and they start womping on us.  They hit the damage shield, since we are all DSed.  I target one, and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Malosini</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  I target the other and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Malosini</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  I know I have targeted a new one because I see its health bar jump a tiny bit, whereas if I target the same one, it does not.  The damage shield makes for a slight variation in the two mobs' health bars, which helps me distinguish them.<br>
<br>
With <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>KEI</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, mana is certainly much less of a problem.<br>
